---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Support" description="Support channels, severity targets, and escalation process.">
  <h1>Support</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--color-text-2); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 32px;">
    Use this process to report bugs, request help, and escalate incidents with actionable evidence.
  </p>

  <h2>Before opening an issue</h2>
  <pre><code style="font-family: var(--font-mono);">voxeltrond --version
voxeltron --version
sudo journalctl -u voxeltrond -n 300 --no-pager</code></pre>

  <h2>Support channels</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>GitHub Issues — reproducible defects</li>
    <li>GitHub Discussions — questions/design feedback</li>
    <li>Discord — quick operator support</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Severity targets (guideline)</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Severity</th><th>Example</th><th>Initial Response Target</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>S1</td><td>Complete outage/data loss risk</td><td>4 hours</td></tr>
      <tr><td>S2</td><td>Deployment blocked for one service</td><td>1 business day</td></tr>
      <tr><td>S3</td><td>Non-blocking bug/workaround exists</td><td>3 business days</td></tr>
      <tr><td>S4</td><td>Docs/usability issue</td><td>5 business days</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Security reporting</h2>
  <div class="callout warning">
    Do not post sensitive security vulnerabilities publicly. Use responsible disclosure channels.
  </div>

  <h2>Feedback incorporation log</h2>
  <p>
    Track accepted feedback and implementation mapping in
    <code>docs/evidence/community/2026-02-26-feedback.md</code>.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
